    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<i>&quot;but that would still require the extra if&quot;</i> - if you don&#39;t want to give one of the items <i>special</i> treatment, then you need to give them all the <i>same</i> treatment. Meaning here, use regex for the validation of <i>all</i> replies, not just a particular one.  Or, have your data structure also contain the information, whether the reply is supposed to be verified by string comparison, or regex. Then you&#39;ll still need an if/else to decide which one to apply - but the necessary info will come from within your data structure itself, so you don&#39;t need to make this dependent on the <i>position</i> of the reply."
